  "summary": "postinstall exfiltrates /etc/passwd to attacker-controlled Pipedream endpoint",
  "details": "package.json declares a postinstall lifecycle script that fires automatically on `npm install`. The script invokes python3 to read the installer's /etc/passwd file and POST its contents over plain HTTP to a hardcoded Pipedream inbox at http://eodxy50gl486xrx.m.pipedream.net. There is no legitimate reason for a package to read and transmit the installer's system account file at install time; this is a direct exfiltration of installer-side data to an attacker-controlled destination.",
